    "body": "## Purpose\n\nThe existing implementation of PDL for the `fused_moe_lora` kernel has a couple issues which don't allow us to realize the full gains of PDL:\n\n\n### 1. `torch.zeros` between shrink and expand calls.\n\nThe call to `torch.zeros` to initialize the intermediate cache occurs between the shrink and expand calls to `fused_moe_lora`. This means we cannot overlap the two `fused_moe_lora` calls via PDL.\n\n![Image 12-15-25 at 12 06 PM](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/da7ff404-db87-41fc-8915-03824193849e)\n\n### 2. Late `gdc_launch_dependents` call\n\nThe invocation of `gdc_launch_dependents` within `fused_moe_lora` occurs after the GEMM is finished, limiting the amount of overlap between shrink and expand, since most of the shrink call is completed by the time expand can begin. The image below shows the shrink/expand overlap after addressing issue number **1** above.\n\n![Image 12-15-25 at 12 09 PM](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/759b90a3-5d73-4312-bed5-231e06ed13e2)\n\n---\n\nThe PR aims to address both of the above issues by (1) initializing the intermediate cache before the shrink invocation of `fused_moe_lora`, and (2) moving the `gdc_launch_dependents` call in shrink to before the GEMM.\n\nThe below image shows the shrink/expand overlap after applying the changes in this PR:\n![Image 12-15-25 at 12 15 PM](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/d8e69bf2-11d9-4bcc-a508-fefedb35abfc)\n\n\n## Test Plan\n\n- [ ] LoRA CI\n- [ ] Benchmarking fused_moe_lora before/after this PR\n\n## Test Result\n\n### Benchmark Results \nBenchmarked gpt-oss-20b w/ concurrency=4, input length=1600, output length=400\n\nBefore\n```\n============ Serving Benchmark Result ============\nSuccessful requests:                     300       \nFailed requests:                         0         \nMaximum request concurrency:             4         \nBenchmark duration (s):                  262.32    \nTotal input tokens:                      481244    \nTotal generated tokens:                  120165    \nRequest throughput (req/s):              1.14      \nOutput token throughput (tok/s):         458.08    \nPeak output token throughput (tok/s):    536.00    \nPeak concurrent requests:                8.00      \nTotal Token throughput (tok/s):          2292.64   \n---------------Time to First Token----------------\nMean TTFT (ms):                          103.96    \nMedian TTFT (ms):                        100.42    \nP99 TTFT (ms):                           183.60    \n-----Time per Output Token (excl. 1st token)------\nMean TPOT (ms):                          8.47      \nMedian TPOT (ms):                        8.46      \nP99 TPOT (ms):                           8.77      \n---------------Inter-token Latency----------------\nMean ITL (ms):                           8.47      \nMedian ITL (ms):                         7.94      \nP99 ITL (ms):                            8.70      \n==================================================\n```\n\nAfter\n```\n============ Serving Benchmark Result ============\nSuccessful requests:                     300       \nFailed requests:                         0         \nMaximum request concurrency:             4         \nBenchmark duration (s):                  242.26    \nTotal input tokens:                      481244    \nTotal generated tokens:                  120165    \nRequest throughput (req/s):              1.24      \nOutput token throughput (tok/s):         496.01    \nPeak output token throughput (tok/s):    592.00    \nPeak concurrent requests:                8.00      \nTotal Token throughput (tok/s):          2482.46   \n---------------Time to First Token----------------\nMean TTFT (ms):                          102.46    \nMedian TTFT (ms):                        97.66     \nP99 TTFT (ms):                           189.00    \n-----Time per Output Token (excl. 1st token)------\nMean TPOT (ms):                          7.80      \nMedian TPOT (ms):                        7.83      \nP99 TPOT (ms):                           8.10      \n---------------Inter-token Latency----------------\nMean ITL (ms):                           7.81      \nMedian ITL (ms):                         7.28      \nP99 ITL (ms):                            8.11      \n==================================================\n```\n\n---\n<details>\n<summary> Essential Elements of an Effective PR Description Checklist </summary>\n\n- [ ] The purpose of the PR, such as \"Fix some issue (link existing issues this PR will resolve)\".\n- [ ] The test plan, such as providing test command.\n- [ ] The test results, such as pasting the results comparison before and after, or e2e results\n- [ ] (Optional) The necessary documentation update, such as updating `supported_models.md` and `examples` for a new model.\n- [ ] (Optional) Release notes update. If your change is user facing, please update the release notes draft in the [Google Doc](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1YyVqrgX4gHTtrstbq8oWUImOyPCKSGnJ7xtTpmXzlRs/edit?tab=t.0).\n</details>\n\n",
